@NODE Aguide28 "DreamDoor.library/FetchKey"

    NAME
        FetchKey - Gets a char or timeout

    SYNOPSIS
        result = FetchKey(dif, flags, timeout)
        D0                 D0   D1    D2
        
        ULONG *GetKey(struct *DIFace, ULONG, ULONG);

    FUNCTION
        This function simply waits for a single keypress from either the
        local console or remote terminal or a timeout. After receiving a
        character or timeout, this function will immediately return with
        no further activity.

    INPUTS
        dif - A Pointer to the DIFace returned by InitDoor()
        flags - currently understands these flags:
                HOTKEY_SHOWCHAR - Show pressed character
                HOTKEY_ADDLF    - Insert CRLF after received character
                HOTKEY_CURSOR   - Check for cursor keys (250=up etc) 
                HOTKEY_DETECT   - Detect origin.
        timeout - timeout in secs
    RESULT
        result - NULL if carrier lost or received character or -1 if
                 timeout occured.

                 If HOTKEY_DETECT was enabled, source of the character
                 is stored in the upper word. (0=Serial, 1=Console)

    SEE ALSO
        GetKey()
@ENDNODE
