@NODE Aguide43 "DreamDoor.library/UpdateUserRec"
DreamDoor.library/UpdateUserRec

    NAME
        UpdateUserRec - Update (current) users data to disk.

    SYNOPSIS
	result = UpdateUserRec( dif,	user )
	D0			D0	D1
        
	ULONG UpdateUserRec(struct *DIFace, struct *user);

    FUNCTION
        Updates a users data to disk in a safe way.

    INPUTS
        dif  - A Pointer to the DIFace returned by InitDoor()
	user - A pointer to a user struct or 0 for online user.

    RESULT
	result - Returns a ptr to the user struct if successful,
		 or 0 for an error.
		 If 0 was specified as user arg, 0 will always
		 be returned.

    NOTES
	It is not currently possible to update the user struct of a
	user that is currently online on another node. This will
	however be supported in the future.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Aguide44 "DreamDoor.library/SetAccPreset"
DreamDoor.library/SetAccPreset

	NAME
		SetAccPreset - Set a users access according to a preset.

    SYNOPSIS
	result = SetAccPreset( dif,	presetid, user )
	D0			D0	D1	  D2

	ULONG SetAccPreset(struct *DIFace, ULONG presetid, struct *user);

    FUNCTION
        Sets a users access preset according to predefined defaults.

    INPUTS
        dif      - A Pointer to the DIFace returned by InitDoor()
	presetid - A valid preset ID (according to the BBS config)
	user     - A pointer to a user struct.

    RESULT
	result	 - Returns 0 for success or anything other for an error.

    NOTES
	You have to update the user struct yourself using the
        UpdateUserRec() function.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Aguide45 "DreamDoor.library/SearchUser"
dreamdoor.library/SearchUser

    NAME
	SearchUser - Search for a specific user by name/handle or userid.

    SYNOPSIS
        result = SearchUser(dif, slot, pat, index, user, flags)
        D0                  d0   d1    d2   d3     d4    d5

	ULONG SearchUser(struct DIFace *, ULONG, char *, ULONG, struct DayDream_User *);

    FUNCTION
        Searches for a user by name, handle or userid. A index-slotnumber may
        be specified to for example continue a search.

    INPUTS
       dif      - A Pointer to the DIFace returned by InitDoor()
       slot     - Slotnumber to search for. Set to -1 if you are searching
                  for a user by name / handle.
       pat      - Name / Handle pattern to search for. Standard AmigaDOS pattern.
                  Should be set to 0 for slot search.
       index    - Set this to continue a namesearch. automaticly ignored in
                  slot search mode.
       user     - A pointer to a user struct. This structure is filled with the
                  found users userstruct (If found ofcourse).

       flags    - SUF_ONLYHANDLES if to search only for handles.
                  SUF_ONLYREALNAMES to search only for realnames.
		  Both theese are naturally only appliable in namesearch mode.

    RESULT
        result - Returns 0 for success or anything else for an error.

    NOTES
        Uses an I/O buffer that makes this routine very fast.

@ENDNODE
